Here's the solution to the problem. The approach uses binary search to find the minimum possible largest sum when splitting the array into `k` subarrays. The idea is to search for the smallest value that can be the maximum sum of any subarray when the array is split into at most `k` parts.

The binary search is performed between the maximum element of the array (as the minimum possible largest sum) and the sum of all elements (as the maximum possible largest sum).

For each candidate value during the binary search, we check if it's possible to split the array into `k` or fewer subarrays such that no subarray has a sum greater than the candidate.

